bib.title: Mining sequential patterns with negative conclusions
bib.author: Kazienko, Przemys{\l}aw
bib.venue: International Conference on Data Warehousing and …
bib.abstract: The new type of patterns: sequential patterns with the negative conclusions is proposed in the paper. They denote that a certain set of items does not occur after a regular frequent sequence. Some experimental results and the SPAWN algorithm for mining sequential patterns with the negative conclusions are also presented.
bib.booktitle: International Conference on Data Warehousing and Knowledge Discovery
